com.softwareag.natural.mapconverter

Interface IConversionListener

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TEXTIDConversionListener

    public interface IConversionListener
    Listeners to the map conversion must implement this interface.

    Besides customization via rules and templates, the map converter can be enhanced via custom conversion listeners. To add a listener, add a variable with the name $$convlistener$$" to your rules file.

    If you would like to add more than one listener use ";" as seperator between the full qualified classnames.

    The classes must be found in the Java classpath of the cisnatural web application. 

      <convvariable dynamic="false" varkind="sys">
       <varname>$$convlistener$$</varname>
       <varvalue>com.somename.MyConversionListener</varvalue>
  </convvariable>
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.1.4.3 $
    Author:
    zim

      • startField

        void startField(IfField field,
                java.util.Map attributeVals)
        Called when the conversion of a <ifField> starts.

        The method is called after the variables and attribute values are resolved according to the default targetitems of the matching rules. The method is called before any targetitem is created.

        Parameters:
        literal - - the ltLiteral as SDO object
        attributeVals - - the attribute values

      • startFieldTarget

        void startFieldTarget(IfField field,
                      java.lang.String targetItem,
                      java.util.Map attributeVals)
        Called when the conversion of a <ifField> for a specific targetitem starts.

        The method is called after the attribute values are resolved according to the conversion rules but before the targetitem is created. Notice that for a single ltLiteral several targetitems can be specified in the conversion rules. In this case this method will be called several times with different targetItem values. The name of the currently processed targetitem is passed to this method.

        Parameters:
        field - - the field as SDO object
        targetItem - - the name of the targetitem as specified in the conversion rules
        attributeVals - the attribute values

      • startLiteral

        void startLiteral(LtLiteral literal,
                  java.util.Map attributeVals)
        Called when the conversion of a <ltLiteral> starts.

        The method is called after the variables and attribute values are resolved according to the default targetitems of the matching rules. The method is called before any targetitem is created.

        Example Usage: A listener can add a textid attribute with the corresponding id as value to the passed attributeVals map. It further can add the text id and translation value to a .csv translation file.

        Parameters:
        literal - - the ltLiteral as SDO object
        attributeVals - - the attribute values

      • startMap

        void startMap(MapxmlPage mapxml)
        Called when the conversion for a Natural map file starts.

        Example Usage:A conversion listener can load/create a corresponding .csv translation file (see Application Designer documentation) to add textids for this map.

        Parameters:
        mapxml - - the mapxml object.
